description: Reserved matters application (conditions 2 and 4) for Phase 3.1 of the Acton Gardens master plan detailing Landscaping, Appearance, Scale, Access and Layout for a part eight to ten storey building containing 124 units (42 one-bedroom, 52 two-bedroom and 30 three-bedroom flats) and podium-level communal gardens; 200sq.m floor space in A1 (retail) / A3 (restaurants / cafes) / B1 (Business) / D1 (Non-residential institutions) use classes; reconfiguration of the public highway; 38 off-street car parking spaces and 22 on-street car parking spaces; public realm landscaping; refuse and bicycle storage, along with the partial discharge of conditions 5 (public realm landscaping), 6, (part) (Energy Strategy), 11 (part) (noise mitigation measures), 18 (part) (tree protection), 19 (refuse & recycling enclosures), 22 (rainwater / greywater), 25 (boundary treatments), 26 (part) (c) and (d) (Secured by Design) pursuant to outline planning permission LBE ref: P/2012/0708 dated 13/08/2013.
decision_conditions: The development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with the following approved plans and documents:   Drawings: (13022) - 001, 010 A, 011, 012, 020, 050, 100 A, 101 A, 110, 111, 112, 113, 114, 115, 116, 117, 118, 150 B, 151, 152, 153, 154, 155, 156, 157, 158, 159, 160, 200, 201, 210, 211, 212, 213, 214, 215, 216, 217, 350, 351, 401, 402, 403, 410; (13104) - P01 A, PH03 A, PP05 A; ITB9027-SK-005 A; A1829/Phase 3.1/Road Surface Layout.  Design and Access Statement (Stitch); Planning Supporting Statement (ref: 180603C, Terence O'Rourke); Statement of Community Involvement (Acton Gardens LLP); Affordable Housing Statement, Estate Management Strategy (London & Quandrant Housing Trust); Updated Phasing Strategy and drawing ref: 020; Phase 1 Habitat Survey (ref: Final, Terence O'Rourke Ltd); Daylight and Sunlight Performance Analysis (Rev: 02, AECOM); Arboricultural Survey (0813-1243 Final, Ruskins); Sustainable Design and Construction Statement - BREEAM Pre-Assessment (ref: J1856 03, Mendick Waring Ltd); Code for Sustainable Homes Pre-Assessment (ref: J1856 02, Mendick Waring Ltd); Energy Strategy (ref: J1856 04, Mendick Waring Ltd); Foul and Surface Water Drainage Scheme (ref: A1829, CTP); Transport Statement (ref: PH/cs/ITB9027-001A R, i-Transport Ltd); Framework Travel Plan (ref: PH/hm/ITB9027-002A R, i-Transport Ltd); Water Statement (ref: J1856 03, Mendick Waring Ltd); Clarification to planning application' regarding electric car charging and entry systems, dated 26/09/2013; Response to Ealing Council Nov-13 ref: J1856 Issue 01 (06/11/2013) prepared by Mendick Waring Ltd; Clarification regarding play equipment (16/12/2013), prepared by BBUK Studio Ltd; Clarification regarding new tree planting species selection (17/12/2013), prepared by BBUK Studio Ltd; Clarification regarding the impact of the revised layout of Stanley Road on existing trees (13/11/2013), prepared by BBUK Studio Ltd; Stage 1 Road Safety Audit (04/11/2013) and addendum ref: MB/2013/9802/RSA1 (13/11/2013), prepared by GM Traffic Consultants Ltd; Clarification in response to Highway officer's comments ref: ITL9027 (08/11/2013) and 'Designer's response to Stage 1 Road Safety Audit for Phases 3.1 and 3.2' ref: PH/RN/ITL9027-005 TN and drawing ITB9027-SK-007, prepared by i-Transport; Noise and Vibration Assessment (ref: DLW/R6702, Acoustical Investigation & Research Organisation Ltd), Clarification  regarding condition 11 (noise mitigation measures) ref: DLW/KH/6702/L1 (05/11/2013) and DLW/KH/6702/L2 (21/11/2013) prepared by Acoustical Investigation & Research Organisation Ltd; Statement on Station Square and Pocket Park, received 06/03/2014.  Reason: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interests of proper planning. | Prior to the commencement of superstructure works, details of the refuse / recycling storage enclosure for the approved A1 / A3 / B1/ D1 Use Class unit shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  Details of a Commercial Services Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the first occupation of the approved A1/ A3/ B1/ D1 Use Class unit.   The approved refuse / recycling storage and servicing arrangements shall be provided in accordance with the approved details.  Reason: To secure the necessary physical waste enclosures to support the development and to ensure that responsible waste management practices are adhered to in accordance with policy 5.17 of the London Plan 2011 and policy 1.1(e) of Ealing's adopted Development (or Core) Strategy 2012.
site_number: Phase 3.1 Wodehouse Court and Woolf Court
